<%# quest-success — generic "+25 seeds!" celebration shown after a quest
    completes OFF the contest page (e.g. a /account username change, where there's
    no quest card to advance in place). Trigger:
      $store.modals.swap('quest-success', { seeds_earned, seeds_total, seeds_level }).

    Contents: a big "+25 seeds" headline, the full seeds progress bar (the same
    components/seeds_bar card variant used in "Earn a Free Entry" — its global
    factory is already loaded by the navbar, so it works when this template is
    cloned in), and — ONLY when the viewer is NOT yet a newsletter subscriber —
    a "Subscribe for +25 more seeds" CTA that hands off to the newsletter-subscribe
    modal. Every modal carries a bottom Close link.

    SINGLE root element (the host mounts this through its own <template x-if>).
    The not-subscribed gate is SERVER-rendered (current_user.subscribed_to_newsletter?)
    so the CTA never flashes for someone who's already in. %>
<div x-data="{ get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} } }">
  <%= render "modals/blocks/card_header",
        size: :lg,
        icon_emoji: "🌱",
        title: "+25 seeds!",
        subtitle: "Nice — that quest is done. Your seeds just went up." %>

  <%# Seeds progress bar — card variant. seeds_data falls back to a zero payload
      when the cache is cold; the seedsBar factory then self-heals from the
      seedsNavbar localStorage value (which StateFanout just bumped), so the bar
      reflects the freshly-earned total either way. %>
  <div class="mb-5">
    <%= render "components/seeds_bar", seeds_data: display_seeds_data, compact: false %>
  </div>

  <% unless current_user.subscribed_to_newsletter? %>
    <button type="button" @click="$store.modals.swap('newsletter-subscribe')"
            class="btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full">
      Subscribe for +25 more seeds
    </button>
  <% end %>

  <button type="button" @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="block mx-auto mt-3 text-sm text-secondary hover:text-heading transition">
    Close
  </button>
</div>
